This paper discusses the use of latent semantic analysis (LSA) to extract semantic meaning from a set of documents. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, given the focus on natural language processing and text analysis, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
